=\frac{(2y-3z)^2-(7z)^2}4=\frac{\{(2y-3z)-7z\}\{(2y-3z)+7z\}}4=\cdots
b^2 - 4ac
\delta = \sqrt {b^2 - 4ac},
 a_1 = \gcd \left( a,    \frac{(b + \delta)}{2}  \right) ; \; \; \; \; \; a_2 = \frac{a}{a_1}  
  a x^2 + b x y + c y^2 =  \; \left(a_2x+ \left( \frac{b + \delta}{2a_1} \right) y \right) \; \; \left(a_1x+ \left( \frac{b - \delta}{2a_2} \right) y \right) \;    
a=1, b= -3, c=-10, b^2 - 4 a c = 49, \delta = 7.
a_1 = 1, a_2 = 1.
(b+\delta)/ (2 a_1) = 4/2 = 2,
(b-\delta)/ (2 a_2) = -10/2 = -5,
x^2 - 3 x y - 10 y^2 = (x + 2 y)(x - 5 y).
y^2-3yz-10z^2=y^2-5yz+2yz-10z^2=y(y-5z)+2z(y-5z)=(y-5z)(y+2z)
